1.title: Robinson
1.plot: Adam Robinson thinks Australia could offer his family the outdoors living they adore. Horse-loving wife Kati isn't ready to join him in the saddle just yet. The couple travel to Perth to see if life down under can be a financial winner.

2.title: Downey
2.plot: When Andrew Downey met Dara he put his lifelong dream of moving to Australia on hold. He now wants to put it back on the family agenda. A trial week in Brisbane sees them checking out properties, work and the lifestyle on offer.

3.title: Hargreaves
3.plot: Childhood holidays in Australia have made Steve Hargreaves determined to make it his home. Wife Diane doesn't share his passion. A trial week down under gives the family the chance to see what sort of life they could have in Perth.

4.title: Graham
4.plot: Dreamer Eric Graham wants to move his whole family to Australia but his wife Rachael is not so sure. A week in Perth sees them check out what life down under has to offer.

5.title: Salaman
5.plot: Australian-born Steve Salaman thinks it's time to return down under for good and his wife Elizabeth is on board but it's a decision that is causing real anguish for daughter Allie.

6.title: Mudhar
6.plot: After a number of failed attempts to move, Jaz Mudhar feels time is running out for her dream of Australia. For husband Jasdeep, however, even the very thought of emigrating fills him with dread.

7.title: Todd
7.plot: Gareth Todd is an optimist who is ready to move to Australia right away. However, it is all proving a bit much for his wife Jodi. In a bid to reach an agreement a trial week in Australia shows the family what the country has to offer.

8.title: Sinfield Day
8.plot: Following a bout of ill health Harriet Sinfield Day wants to make every day count, her husband David wants to do whatever he can to make her happy but has serious doubts about leaving behind their life in the UK.

9.title: Witte
9.plot: Jayne Witte is at her wits' end with the weather in Wales and would like to move her family to the sunnier climes of Australia. First she needs to get husband Gavin on board and a trial week in Brisbane could be the answer.

10.title: Walker
10.plot: Holly Walker is thinking of starting a new life on the other side of the world but her husband Rob doesn't think the grass will be any greener down under. Will a week in Nelson, New Zealand change his mind?

11.title: Parker
11.plot: Jo Parker is ready to move to Australia, but with their son having special needs, Jo's wife Mandy isn't convinced that it is the practical thing to do. A week in Melbourne sees the family sample life down under.

12.title: Donnelly
12.plot: When Lynne met Alan Donnelly, she put a lifelong dream of moving to Australia on hold. Now she wants it back on the family agenda, but her husband Alan is not convinced.

13.title: McEleney
13.plot: Ciara McEleney wants to move her whole family to Australia for one main reason - the weather. Her husband Ruairi, however, is proving to be a cloud on her new horizons.

14.title: Baker
14.plot: Nathaniel Baker believes his family's future lies down under, but his wife Gemma sees things very differently. The family experience a trial week in Melbourne to learn about life down under.

15.title: Ballentine-Brain
15.plot: The Ballentine-Brain family are split down the middle about where they want to spend the rest of their lives. South African-born Zelease wants the warmth of Australia, while husband Matt thinks sense and stability lies in Britain.

16.title: Tomkins
16.plot: Amanda Tomkins wants to take her family and move to the other side of the world. But husband Mike and son Harvey are far from sold on the idea.

17.title: Blacklidge/Horastead
17.plot: Carly Blacklidge feels stuck in a rut and that New Zealand might be the answer. But husband Jason knows if they move there - to the other side of the world - he might never see his elderly parents again.

18.title: McCalla
18.plot: Leona McCalla fell for the Aussie lifestyle on previous trips down under and now wants to make it her home for good. All she has to do is convince her husband and daughters it is worth giving up their comfortable life in the UK for.

19.title: McDonald
19.plot: Paul McDonald has a dream and he is determined to make it come true, but his wife Christine loves her life in the heart of north east England.

20.title: Williams
20.plot: Geraint Williams is getting itchy feet and feels New Zealand provides just the cure, but his wife Rebecca dreads leaving her close Welsh family behind - including her elderly parents.

21.title: Langridge
21.plot: Abigail Langridge is convinced her family needs a new start if they are to get the most out of life, but her husband and son simply don't want to go.

22.title: Goodwin-Barker
22.plot: Steff Barker is obsessed with all things New Zealand - including moving there. Her husband Alan Goodwin, however, finds even the idea of a move painful.

23.title: Johnson
23.plot: Gill Johnson wants to move down under and sees this as her last chance to move. Her husband Mark wants to support his wife but as an only child has split loyalties.

24.title: Price
24.plot: Ever since getting married in Australia, Lee Price has dreamed of living happily ever after down under with his wife Amanda. Now, with their children growing up, it is back on the agenda.

25.title: Selby
25.plot: 6 years ago Kim Selby was struck down by serious illness. Having pulled through, her get up and go knows no bounds. Problem is she wants to do it in Australia but her eldest daughter's not for budging.

imdb.plot outline: If the job that you do is on the list of those in short supply in Australia, you are under 45 and you are thinking of emigrating then the Australian government will help to fast track you through the immigration procedure. The BBC has found 20 such families and offers them a chance to sample life Down Under for a week to help make the decision.
imdb.title: Wanted Down Under
plot: If the job that you do is on the list of those in short supply in Australia, you are under 45 and you are thinking of emigrating then the Australian government will help to fast track you through the immigration procedure. The BBC has found 20 such families and offers them a chance to sample life Down Under for a week to help make the decision.::Mark Smith <msmith@osi.co.uk>
